<document id="22765848"><sentence text="Treatment of chronic pain in older people: evidence-based choice of strong-acting opioids." /><sentence text="In the treatment of chronic malignant and non-malignant pain, opioids are used as strong analgesics" /><sentence text=" Frail elderly patients often have multiple co-morbidities and use multiple medicines, leading to an increased risk of clinically relevant drug-drug and drug-disease interactions" /><sentence text=" Age-related changes and increased frailty may lead to a less predictable drug response, increased drug sensitivity, and potential harmful drug effects" /><sentence text=" As a result, physicians face a complex task in prescribing medication to elderly patients" /><sentence text=" In this review, the appropriateness of the strong-acting opioids buprenorphine, fentanyl, hydromorphone, methadone, morphine, oxycodone and tapentadol is determined for use in elderly patients"><entity charOffset="66-79" id="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e0" text="buprenorphine" /><entity charOffset="81-89" id="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e1" text="fentanyl" /><entity charOffset="91-104" id="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e2" text="hydromorphone" /><entity charOffset="106-115" id="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e3" text="methadone" /><entity charOffset="117-125" id="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e4" text="morphine" /><entity charOffset="127-136" id="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e5" text="oxycodone" /><entity charOffset="141-151" id="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e6" text="tapentadol" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e0" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e1" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e2" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e3" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e4" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e5" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e6" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e1" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e2" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e3" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e4" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e5" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e6" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e2" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e2" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e2" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e3" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e2" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e4" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e2" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e5" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e2" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e6" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e3" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e3" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e3" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e4" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e3" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e5" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e3" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e6" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e4" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e4" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e4" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e5" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e4" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e6" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e5" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e5" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e5" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s6.e6" /></sentence><sentence text=" Evidence-based recommendations for prescribing strong opioids to the frail elderly are presented" /><sentence text=" A literature search was performed for all individual drugs, using a validated and published set of 23 criteria concerning effectiveness, safety, pharmacokinetics and pharmacodynamics, experience, and convenience in elderly patients" /><sentence text=" First, information on the criteria was obtained from pharmaceutical reference books and a MEDLINE search" /><sentence text=" The information obtained on the individual drugs in the class of opioids was compared with the reference drug morphine"><entity charOffset="111-119" id="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s10.e0" text="morphine" /></sentence><sentence text=" Evidence-based recommendations were formulated on the basis of the pros and cons for the frail elderly" /><sentence text=" Using the set of 23 criteria, no differentiation can be made between the appropriateness of buprenorphine, fentanyl, hydromorphone, morphine and oxycodone for use in elderly patients"><entity charOffset="93-106" id="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e0" text="buprenorphine" /><entity charOffset="108-116" id="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e1" text="fentanyl" /><entity charOffset="118-131" id="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e2" text="hydromorphone" /><entity charOffset="133-141" id="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e3" text="morphine" /><entity charOffset="146-155" id="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e4" text="oxycodone" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e0" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e1" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e2" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e3" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e4" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e1" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e2" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e3" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e4" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e2" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e2" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e2" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e3" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e2" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e4" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e3" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e3" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e3" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s12.e4" /></sentence><sentence text=" Methadone has strong negative considerations in the treatment of chronic pain in the frail elderly"><entity charOffset="1-10" id="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s13.e0" text="Methadone" /></sentence><sentence text=" Methadone has a high drug-drug interaction potential and is associated with prolongation of the QT interval and a potential risk of accumulation due to a long elimination half-life"><entity charOffset="1-10" id="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s14.e0" text="Methadone" /></sentence><sentence text=" In addition, methadone is difficult to titrate because of its large inter-individual variability in pharmacokinetics, particularly in the frail elderly"><entity charOffset="14-23" id="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s15.e0" text="methadone" /></sentence><sentence text=" Because of a lack of empiric knowledge, the use of tapentadol is not recommended in frail elderly persons"><entity charOffset="52-62" id="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s16.e0" text="tapentadol" /></sentence><sentence text=" Nevertheless, tapentadol may prove to be a useful analgesic for the treatment of chronic pain in frail elderly persons because of its possible better gastrointestinal tolerability"><entity charOffset="15-25" id="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s17.e0" text="tapentadol" /></sentence><sentence text=" In the treatment of chronic pain in the frail elderly, the opioids of first choice are buprenorphine, fentanyl, hydromorphone, morphine and oxycodone"><entity charOffset="88-101" id="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e0" text="buprenorphine" /><entity charOffset="103-111" id="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e1" text="fentanyl" /><entity charOffset="113-126" id="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e2" text="hydromorphone" /><entity charOffset="128-136" id="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e3" text="morphine" /><entity charOffset="141-150" id="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e4" text="oxycodone" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e0" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e1" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e2" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e3" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e4" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e1" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e2" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e3" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e4" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e2" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e2" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e2" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e3" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e2" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e4" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e3" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e3" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e3" e2="DDI-PubMed.22765848.s18.e4" /></sentence><sentence text=" In order to improve the convenience for elderly patients, the controlled-release oral dosage forms and transdermal formulations are preferred" /><sentence text="" /></document>